        "There are two main reasons why a smaller number of people walk on a daily basic. Firstly, many people tend to have morden sedentary lifestyle, it leads to walking is a luxury. The more spend time sitting in the classrooms or offices, the less chance of going for a stroll. Secondaly, the covenience of motor vehicles lures many away from daily walks. Normally, motorists and public transport users enjoy commute. Because it is be freed from different weather conditions dust and other pollutants.",
        "There are actions that could be implemented to address the public have lost the habit of walking regularly. Headmasters and business leaders lauch campaigns promoting regular walks. For an example, in lower-rise schools and office buildings, taking stairs should be prioritized over the lift. Furthermore, health experts raise public awarness of the benefits associated with brisk walking and warn against passive lifestyle. Once better- informed people feel motivated to incorporate a walk into their daily routine such as walking to the nearest destinations.",
